Comment.Text: Acquiring the data from data file -> Select the reference channels -> Bandpass filter for whole range of frequencies -> Bandstop filters in series to cut off unwanted frequencies (keep wanted frequencies) -> Spatial filter to get the electrodes that contribute the most to variance -> Epoch data based on label put on the data -> Break the data into 4 signals with the same frequency range as our classes -> Run the signal through a DSP formula -> Aggregate the signals into a single feature -> Train the classifier
Need to reconfigure Generic Stream Reader, Spatial Filter box, and Classifier Trainer to correct directory Generic Stream Reader should be training data

Reference The stimulation codes will be: OVTK_GDF_Up (7 Hz) OVTK_GDF_Right (9 Hz) OVTK_GDF_Left (11 Hz) OVTK_GDF_Down (13 Hz) OVTK_StimulationId_Label_01 (End Label) OVTK_StimulationId_Label_09 (Looking away) OVTK_StimulationId_Label_0A (Closed Eyes)
